The paper deals with learning how to simulate realistic collective motion of zebrafish using real-world tracking data, which involves the use of artificial neural networks and agent-based models. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA), Robotics (cs.RO), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Machine Learning (cs.LG).
